The paper deals with reverse engineering problems for conjunctive queries, which are commonly used in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity analysis and graph theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper proposes relaxations of the problems, which could be seen as an AI approach (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problems, which could also be related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
